Date: Mon, 20 Jul 2026 22:46:58 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 63/64] web-app: unread-only filter toggle in the chat list

Add a borderless filter button to the chat list header (next to search) that
filters the list to chats with fresh messages, using core's `is:unread`
chatlist query composed with any typed search text.

The toggle keys the query off `is:unread` but leaves `isSearchActive` on the
raw typed text, so filtering alone shows the plain chat list rather than
entering search-results mode. The archive view keeps DC_GCL_ARCHIVED_ONLY.

While the filter is active a "Unread: N chats" heading (a search-result-divider,
mirroring search-in-chat) is shown above the list. The toggle uses a Material
filter_list icon.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
